---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Badge from '../components/ui/Badge.astro';
import Mermaid from '../components/Mermaid.astro';
import Card from '../components/ui/Card.astro';
import CardHeader from '../components/ui/CardHeader.astro';
import CardTitle from '../components/ui/CardTitle.astro';
import CardContent from '../components/ui/CardContent.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction" currentPath={`${base}/`}>
  <Badge variant="outline" class="not-prose text-muted-foreground mb-4">
    Last updated Apr 2026
  </Badge>
  <h1>State of State Management</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground !mt-2">
    A comparison of state management architectures across Web, iOS, and Android.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Two Independent Axes</h2>

  <p>This report organizes the state management landscape along two independent axes:</p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong><a href={`${base}/push-vs-pull/`}>Push vs Pull</a></strong> — how state changes flow to consumers</li>
    <li><strong>Graph-based dependency tracking</strong> — a technique for managing derived state, applicable to either push or pull systems</li>
  </ol>

  <p>Push and Pull describe the <strong>direction of data flow</strong>. Graph describes <strong>how derived state dependencies are managed</strong> — and it can appear in both push and pull architectures.</p>

  <div class="not-prose mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">
          Push-based
        </CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Mermaid chart={`
graph TD
  Store["🔄 Store"]
  Store -->|notify| SubA["Sub A"]
  Store -->|notify| SubB["Sub B"]
  Store -->|notify| SubC["Sub C"]
  SubA -->|"selector ✓"| RenderA["re-render"]
  SubB -->|"selector ✗"| Skip["skip"]
  SubC -->|"selector ✓"| RenderC["re-render"]
`} />
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">
          Pull-based
        </CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Mermaid chart={`
graph TD
  Count["count ●"]
  User["user"]
  Count --> Doubled["doubled"]
  Count --> Filtered["filtered"]
  User -.-> Greeting["greeting"]
  Doubled --> RenderA["re-render"]
  Filtered --> RenderB["re-render"]
`} />
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <h2>Graph-based Dependency Tracking</h2>

  <p><strong>Every state management system needs derived state.</strong> Whether push or pull, applications inevitably need to compute values from other values — filtered lists, aggregated counts, combined UI states.</p>

  <p>The question is: <strong>how are the dependencies between source and derived state managed?</strong></p>

  <h3>1. Automatic / Implicit</h3>
  <p>The act of "reading" a state node automatically registers a dependency.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Jotai</strong>: <code>atom(get =&gt; get(otherAtom))</code></li>
    <li><strong>Atoms</strong>: <code>context.watch(OtherAtom())</code> (push propagation)</li>
    <li><strong>Riverpod</strong>: <code>ref.watch(provider)</code> (push propagation)</li>
    <li><strong>swift-state-graph</strong>: ThreadLocal access observation</li>
    <li><strong>Jetpack Compose</strong>: Snapshot system in <code>derivedStateOf {"{}"}</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2. Explicit / Declarative</h3>
  <p>The developer declares dependencies via a <code>deps</code> array or pipeline.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>TanStack Store</strong>: <code>new Derived({"{ deps: [storeA, storeB], fn: ... }"})</code></li>
    <li><strong>Verge</strong>: <code>store.derived(.select(\.count))</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3. No Graph (Manual)</h3>
  <p>No dependency graph. The developer wires everything by hand.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Zustand</strong>: Selectors with <code>Object.is</code> equality</li>
    <li><strong>TCA</strong>: Computed properties on State struct</li>
    <li><strong>StateFlow</strong>: <code>combine(a, b) {"{ ... }"}</code></li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Cross-platform Summary</h2>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 w-full overflow-auto rounded-lg border border-border bg-card">
    <table class="w-full min-w-[600px] caption-bottom text-sm">
      <thead class="[&_tr]:border-b">
        <tr class="border-b transition-colors">
          <th class="h-10 px-4 text-left align-middle font-medium text-muted-foreground">Platform</th>
          <th class="h-10 px-4 text-left align-middle font-medium text-muted-foreground">Push-based (Mainstream)</th>
          <th class="h-10 px-4 text-left align-middle font-medium text-muted-foreground">Pull-based / Graph (Emerging)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="[&_tr:last-child]:border-0">
        <tr class="border-b transition-colors hover:bg-muted/50">
          <td class="p-4 align-middle font-medium text-foreground"><a href={`${base}/web/`} class="underline underline-offset-4">Web</a></td>
          <td class="p-4 align-middle text-muted-foreground">Redux, Zustand</td>
          <td class="p-4 align-middle text-muted-foreground">Jotai, Signals, TanStack Store (push+graph)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b transition-colors hover:bg-muted/50">
          <td class="p-4 align-middle font-medium text-foreground"><a href={`${base}/ios/`} class="underline underline-offset-4">iOS</a></td>
          <td class="p-4 align-middle text-muted-foreground">Verge, TCA</td>
          <td class="p-4 align-middle text-muted-foreground">Atoms (push+graph), swift-state-graph</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b transition-colors hover:bg-muted/50">
          <td class="p-4 align-middle font-medium text-foreground"><a href={`${base}/android/`} class="underline underline-offset-4">Android</a></td>
          <td class="p-4 align-middle text-muted-foreground">ViewModel + StateFlow</td>
          <td class="p-4 align-middle text-muted-foreground">Compose derivedStateOf (UI layer only)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="transition-colors hover:bg-muted/50">
          <td class="p-4 align-middle font-medium text-foreground"><a href={`${base}/flutter/`} class="underline underline-offset-4">Flutter</a></td>
          <td class="p-4 align-middle text-muted-foreground">Provider, Bloc</td>
          <td class="p-4 align-middle text-muted-foreground">Riverpod (push+graph)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
